paragraphs.title: Get Historical Data From Yahoo
paragraphs.text:
//format inputs
import java.util.Date
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat
import java.util.Calendar
import sys.process._

val now = Calendar.getInstance()
val currentDate = now.get(Calendar.YEAR) + "-" + (now.get(Calendar.MONTH)+1) + "-" + now.get(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH)

val from = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(fromDate)
val to   = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(currentDate)
val (fd,fm,fy) = (new SimpleDateFormat("dd").format(from), from.getMonth, (1900 +from.getYear))
val (td,tm,ty) = (new SimpleDateFormat("dd").format(to),   to.getMonth,   (1900 +to.getYear))

case class Security(sym: String, secType: String, secDetail: String, group: Int)
val investmentMenuList = List(Security("VLACX", "Equity", "LgCap", 1), Security("FLCSX", "Equity", "LgCap", 2), Security("TRULX", "Equity", "LgCap", 3), Security("VIMSX", "Equity", "MidCap", 1), Security("FMCSX", "Equity", "MidCap", 2), Security("WFMDX", "Equity", "MidCap", 3), Security("NAESX", "Equity","SmCap", 1), Security("WFSSX", "Equity","SmCap", 2), Security("FSLCX", "Equity","SmCap", 3), Security("VBMFX", "Bond", "Domestic", 1), Security("FBIDX", "Bond", "Domestic", 2), Security("WMFDX", "Bond", "Domestic", 3), Security("VTMGX", "Bond","DevInt", 1), Security("ESICX", "Bond","DevInt", 2), Security("FGBFX", "Bond","DevInt", 3), Security("TPINX", "Bond", "Emerging", 1), Security("VEIEX","Bond","Emerging", 2), Security("FNMIX","Bond","Emerging", 3), Security("GLD", "Other", "PMetal", 1), Security("SLV", "Other", "PMetal", 2), Security("PPLT", "Other", "PMetal", 3), Security("FCSSX", "Other", "Commodities", 1), Security("DBC", "Other", "Commodities", 2), Security("JNK", "Other", "Commodities", 3))

///var securities:Map[String,Security] = scala.collection.mutable.Map()
//securities += (key -> value)

def getWeekOfMonth(currentDate: Date): Int = { 
    val workingDate = Calendar.getInstance() 
    workingDate.setTime(currentDate)
    val week = workingDate.get(Calendar.WEEK_OF_YEAR)
    week
}

val investmentMenuDF = sc.parallelize(investmentMenuList).toDF
investmentMenuDF.registerTempTable("InvestmentMenu")

case class StockData (sym : String, Date: java.sql.Date, Open :Double, High : Double, Low: Double, Close:Double, Volume: Int, AdjClose: Double, Year: Int, day: Int, month: Int, WeekOfYear: Int, DayOfWeek: Int)

//val curlStrs = stocks.map(symbol => (symbol, s"http://ichart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s=$symbol&a=$fm&b=$fd&c=$fy&d=$tm&e=$td&f=$ty&g=d&ignore=.csv" ))
val curlStrs = investmentMenuList.map(security => (security.sym, s"http://ichart.finance.yahoo.com/table.csv?s="+security.sym+"&a=$fm&b=$fd&c=$fy&d=$tm&e=$td&f=$ty&g=d&ignore=.csv"))
val data = curlStrs.map{ case (sym, curlStr) => 
                            ("curl -s "+ curlStr !!)    // for each symbol call yahoo
                            .split("\n")                                             // split the data into rows
                            .tail                                                  // get all lines except header
                            .map(_.split(","))                                     // put cols into array
                            .map(x => StockData(sym, new java.sql.Date(new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(x(0)).getTime), x(1).toDouble, x(2).toDouble, x(3).toDouble, x(4).toDouble, x(5).toInt, x(6).toDouble, new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(x(0)).getYear+1900, new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(x(0)).getDate, new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(x(0)).getMonth+1, getWeekOfMonth(new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(x(0))) , new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd").parse(x(0)).getDay)) }.flatten

val dataDF = sc.parallelize(data)
dataDF.cache

val dataDFF = dataDF.toDF
dataDFF.registerTempTable("data")
sqlContext.cacheTable("data") 

val portfolioPricesDF = sqlContext.sql("select sym, date, close from data, (select max(date) as maxDate from data) as maxDateTable where date = maxDate")
portfolioPricesDF.registerTempTable("PortfolioPrices")
sqlContext.cacheTable("PortfolioPrices")

//portfolioPricesDF.show
investmentMenuDF.show

paragraphs.title: Run Monte Carlo Simulation
Portfolio Stats
paragraphs.text:
%sql select sym, meanPrice, concat(avgReturn, "%") as totalReturn, stndDev, 
concat (ratio * 100, "%") as `ratio %`, 
initialAmt, (initialAmt + initialAmt * (avgReturn * 0.01 )) as currentValue  
from stats

%sql 

select `interval`, simNum, sum(currentValue) as currentValue from PricedSimulation group by `interval`, simNum order by simNum, `interval`

%sql

--select `interval`, explode (endingValue) as endingValue

            select `interval`, simNum, sum(currentValue) as currentValue
